text.tspan: Each enzyme contains a gid of 100 boxes.
Each box represents a single genome and
is either colored based on the taxonomy
of the organism, or is left blank if no gene
is annotated for that reaction in that genome.
The order of the rows and columns is left-to-right
top-to-bottom. If less than 100 genomes are
used, then a number of boxes will always be blank
towards the end. To the right is the color pattern
if all genomes contained a particular reaction.
